snippet.textDisplay: Guys, you know your stuff, and I love your Genuine Bad * Chevrolet!!! I'm going to tell you some rock bottom truth here because I want you to be most successful as possible. In todays times, 22lbs. is getting to be the norm and common number everybody likes. and easy too much boost to run, to make it reliable, while also being consistently driven. Kudos to the driver in his warning to start @16lbs. He would have been solid if everyone would have been happy staying at 16lb. Being limited only because of the head gasket in this particular application, 22lb. is asking a little too much. You want 22 lbs. every pass? Have your local machine guys, (someone whom is known as a respected machinist), to put together a screamer that will only need 7k (rpms), and will do so for many years. Is there a different head gasket, or head that's better suited for this combination? Or is this the dominate head/gasket combo?
